The paper deals with the concept of Restricted Isometry Constants (RIC) which is a fundamental concept in compressed sensing and has applications in various areas of computer science such as signal processing, machine learning, and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the analysis of singular values of matrices, which is a common topic in machine learning and data analysis, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization techniques to derive the bounds, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial analysis, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of random matrices, which is a common topic in statistics and probability, making cs.SI (Statistics) a possible sub-category.
